	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Monomer ORP2 transfer Cholesterol, homotetrameric ORP2 -PI4,5P2 (Based on structural information, the cholesterol‐bound ORP2 is monomeric and the PI(4,5)P2‐bound one tetrameric (Wang et␣al, 2019), i.e., four cholesterol molecules would be transported from late to recycling organelles by ORP2 monomers that assemble to a tetramer to transport four PI(4,5)P2 molecules back)"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
